section.section:
A certificate of trust filed by a statutory trust with the Department shall set forth:
The name of the statutory trust;
The name and the business address of the resident agent;
The address of the principal office of the statutory trust in the State;
Any notice provided in accordance with § 12-501(d) of this title; and
Any other matters the trustees determine to include in the certificate of trust.

The restated certificate of trust shall be specifically designated as a restated certificate of trust in its heading and shall set forth:
The present name of the statutory trust;
The date of filing of the original certificate of trust with the Department;
The information required to be included in accordance with subsection (a) of this section; and
Any other information the trustees determine to include in the restated certificate of trust.
